edu.performance.test.floatoperation

Class FloatOperation

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.performance.test.PerformanceTest<java.lang.Double>
      • edu.performance.test.floatoperation.FloatOperation

  • public class FloatOperation
extends PerformanceTest<java.lang.Double>
    This class extends FloatOperation and it executes operations with double float point number. Currently this operations are - Square root calculation by Newton method - Sine calculation from Math library - Pi calculation by MonteCarlo method - Linpack
    Author:
    Thiago

      • testAFloatOperationLinpack

        void testAFloatOperationLinpack(double level)
        This method executes Linpack benchmark using the implementation posted in http://www.jeckle.de/freeStuff/jLinpack/Linpack.java (09/06/2014). Linpack solves a dense n by n system of linear equations Ax = b. In this test the n is determinate by level.
        Parameters:
        level - Define the dimension of linear equation system. Max.: 1000
